{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 13:49:13.115400", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Diagnostic report — multi-tier Clos EBGP lab\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- The network fabric (routers: leafs, spines, super-spine) is functioning normally: BGP sessions are established and inter-router /31 links and routes are present and populated.\\n- One clear anomaly: host pc_0_1 is not configured with an IP address and is therefore unreachable. This is the only host-level failure detected; the routing control plane and inter-router forwarding appear healthy.\\n\\nTests performed (commands / tool results used)\\n- Global reachability sweep (get_reachability): many hosts reachable; pings sourced from pc_0_1 returned \"unknown\".\\n- Collected host network configs (ip addr, ifconfig, ip route) for pc_0_0, pc_0_1 and all routers (leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0).\\n- BGP summaries from leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0 (frr show ip bgp summary).\\n- Attempted ping from leaf_router_0_1 to pc_0_1 (failed because pc_0_1 has no IP).\\n- Direct ip addr/route check on pc_0_1.\\n\\nFindings and evidence\\n\\n1) Host pc_0_1 has no IP address configured (primary anomaly)\\n- pc_0_1 ip output: only loopback present (no eth0 IP).\\n  Evidence: exec_shell on pc_0_1 returned only the lo interface (inet 127.0.0.1/8), no 10.0.1.2 or any address.\\n- Ping attempt from leaf_router_0_1 to pc_0_1 failed because the tool could not determine pc_0_1\\'s IP: \"Cannot get IP address of host pc_0_1.\"\\n- get_reachability results: any tests with src pc_0_1 show status \"unknown\" (consistent with pc_0_1 not responding / missing address).\\n\\n2) Leaf router facing pc_0_1 appears up and advertising the pod subnet\\n- leaf_router_0_1 has eth4 configured as 10.0.1.1/24 and shows the 10.0.1.0/24 network as directly connected in its kernel routes.\\n  Evidence: leaf_router_0_1 ip_addr shows \"inet 10.0.1.1/24 scope global eth4\" and ip_route includes \"10.0.1.0/24 dev eth4 proto kernel scope link src 10.0.1.1\".\\n- However, leaf_router_0_1\\'s eth4 counters show RX packets 0 and TX packets 0 — no L2 traffic to a host (supports that the host either is down or not responding at L3).\\n  Evidence: ifconfig eth4: \"RX packets 0 bytes 0 ... TX packets 0 bytes 0\".\\n\\n3) Control plane (BGP) appears stable and consistent\\n- BGP neighbors are established on all routers in the fabric:\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 summary: 4 neighbors, all in State/PfxRcd showing prefixes (neighbors up; PfxRcd 7).\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 summary: neighbors established (PfxRcd values present).\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: each show 6 peers and established sessions.\\n  - super_spine_router_0: shows 8 neighbors and sessions up.\\n  Evidence: outputs from frr show ip bgp summary for each router show MsgRcvd/MsgSent counters and PfxRcd values; no neighbor in Idle/Connect/Active.\\n\\n4) Data-plane routing entries present and consistent\\n- Routers\\' kernel/FIB have learned the /24 host networks via BGP (10.0.0.0/24 .. 10.1.3.0/24 appear in routing tables with next-hops through proper interfaces).\\n  Evidence: super_spine_router_0 frr_show_ip_route output shows B>* entries for 10.0.x.0/24 and 10.1.x.0/24 with next-hops; leaf routers show direct connected /24 for their access network.\\n\\nLocalization of fault\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (host).\\n- Fault location: host-side (L3 config missing). The access leaf (leaf_router_0_1) is up and advertising 10.0.1.0/24; the issue is on the host itself (no IP configured). Layer 1/2 at the leaf appears up (interface exists), but no traffic to the host port is observed.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- Immediate root cause: pc_0_1 does not have a configured IP address (no eth0/host IP); therefore it cannot participate in network communication. This could be due to the host being down, interface missing, or no DHCP/static IP assigned; based on gathered evidence, the host OS shows only loopback and no host-facing interface address.\\n- There is no evidence of BGP or fabric-level failure: BGP sessions, inter-router /31 links, and routes are present. The leaf-router is advertising/has the access-subnet configured, so the misbehavior is isolated to the host endpoint.\\n\\nAdditional observations\\n- pc_0_0 is correctly configured (10.0.0.2/24) and reachable; leaf_router_0_0 eth4 shows RX/TX activity (consistent).\\n- All BGP sessions show recent Up times and prefixes exchanged — no control-plane flaps detected in the collected snapshots.\\n- Interface counters on leaf_router_0_1 eth4 are zero (no traffic to host); corroborates host-side absence of IP/traffic.\\n\\nSummary conclusion\\n- Network fabric and routing are healthy (BGP and routing tables consistent). The only abnormal behavior is an unreachable/misconfigured host: pc_0_1 has no IP address and is therefore not reachable. Root cause is local to pc_0_1 (host-side configuration or host down). No further anomalies in the fabric were detected from the data collected.\\n\\nIf you want, I can (only upon your request) run further checks limited to the faulty host (e.g., show its interface link state, dmesg, or attempt to configure/inspect eth0), or gather ARP/neighbor tables on leaf_router_0_1 to confirm L2 status. (Note: per your instructions I have not suggested or applied any mitigations.), please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='41ea7f1c-5e1c-448f-959b-080a1fc24a53'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5-mini", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
